[0.005, "o", "\u001b[1;8He INI constants (On, Off, True, False, Yes, No and None) or an \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fpre\u001b[2;4He.g. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted string (\"bar\"), or a reference\u001b[3;5Heviously set variable or directive (e\u001b[5;7Hessions in the INI file are limited to bitwise operators and parenthese\u001b[6;12He\u001b[7;12He\u001b[8;12He\u001b[9;12He\u001b[10;10He\u001b[12;7Hean flags can be turned on using the values 1, On, True or Ye\u001b[13;5Hey can be turned off using the values 0, Off, False\u001b[15;6Hempty string can be denoted by simply not writing anything after the e\u001b[16;23He None ke\u001b[18;20Hets foo to an e\u001b[19;12He    ; sets foo to an e\u001b[20;13He\"  ; sets foo to the string 'None\u001b[22;12He constants in your value, and these constants be\u001b[23;19Hed \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000ftension (either a PHP \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000ftension or a Zend \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fte\u001b[24;18He these constants *after* the line that loads the \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fte\u001b[27;17He\u001b[29;10Hes packaged with two INI files. One that is recommended to be use\u001b[30;17Henvironments and one that is recommended to be use\u001b[31;4Hevelopment environme\u001b[33;32Hettings which hold security, performance\u001b[34;4Hest practices at its core. But please be aware, these settings may bre\u001b[35;25Her or less security-conscious applications. We\u001b[36;4Hecommending using the production ini in production and testing environme\u001b[38;12Hevelopment is very similar to its production variant, \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fce\u001b[39;11He verbose when it comes to errors. We recommend using the\u001b[40;4Hevelopment version only in development environments, as e\u001b[41;17Hers can inadvertently leak otherwise secure\u001b[43;13He php.ini-production INI file\u001b[46;10Heference\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f81,66\u001b[48;4H\u001b[?25h"]
