[0.005, "o", "\u001b[1;3Hhttps://php.net/ignore-user-abort\u001b[45X\u001b[2;2Hignore_user_abort = On\u001b[49X\r\n\u001b[52X\n; Determines the size of the realpath cache to be used by PHP. This value should\u001b[5;3Hbe increased on systems where PHP opens many files to reflect the quantity of\u001b[6;3Hthe file operations performed.\u001b[7;3HNote: if open_basedir is set, the cache is disabled\u001b[8;3Hhttps://php.net/realpath-cache-size\u001b[9;2Hrealpath_cache_size = 4096k\r\n\u001b[16X\n; Duration of time, in seconds for which to cache realpath information for a given\u001b[12;3Hfile or directory. For systems with rarely changing files, consider increasing this\u001b[13;3Hvalue.\u001b[54X\r\n; https://php.net/realpath-cache-ttl\u001b[15;2Hrealpath_cache_ttl = 120\u001b[54X\r\n\u001b[37X\n; Enables or disables the circular reference collector.\u001b[18;3Hhttps://php.net/zend.enable-gc\u001b[13X\r\nzend.enable_gc =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[26X\r\n\u001b[47X\n; If enabled, scripts may be written in encodings that are incompatible with\u001b[22;3Hthe scanner.  CP936, Big5, CP949 and Shift_JIS are the examples of such\u001b[23;3Hencodings.  To use this feature, mbstring \u001b[30m\u001b[103mext\u001b[m\u000fension must be enabled.\u001b[6X\u001b[24;2Hzend.multibyte = Off\u001b[56X\u001b[26;2H Allows to set the default encoding for the scripts.  This value will be used\u001b[27;3Hunless \"declare(encoding=...)\" directive appears at the top of the script.\u001b[28;2H Only affects if zend.multibyte is set.\u001b[29;2Hzend.script_encoding =\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[70X\u001b[31;3HAllows to include or exclude arguments from stack traces generated for exceptions.\r\n; In production, it is recommended to turn this setting on to prohibit the output\u001b[33;3Hof sensitive information in stack traces\u001b[33X\u001b[34;3HDefault Value: Off\u001b[55X\u001b[35;3HDevelopment Value: Off\u001b[46X\u001b[36;3HProduction Value: On\u001b[57X\r\nzend.exception_ignore_args =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[39;3HAllows setting the maximum string length in an argument of a stringified stack trace\u001b[40;3Hto a value between 0 and 1000000.\u001b[39X\u001b[41;3HThis has no effect when zend.exception_ignore_args is enabled.\u001b[8X\r\n; Default Value: 15\u001b[43;3HDevelopment Value: 15\u001b[19X\r\n; Production Value: 0\u001b[45;2H In production, it is recommended to set this to 0 to reduce the output\u001b[46;3Hof sensitive information in stack traces.\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f360,45         18\u001b[48;5H\u001b[?25h"]
