[59.142, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000f\r\u001b[48;1H\u001b[10X\u001b[1;3Hof the INI constants (On, Off, True, False, Yes, No and None) or an expression\u001b[2;2H (e.g. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted string (\"bar\"), or a reference to a\r\n; previously set variable or directive (e.g. ${foo})\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[5;3HExpressions in the INI file are limited to bitwise operators and parentheses:\u001b[6;3H|  bitwise OR\u001b[17X\u001b[7;3H^  bitwise XOR\u001b[37X\u001b[8;3H&  bitwise AND\u001b[21X\u001b[9;2H ~  bitwise NOT\u001b[12X\r\n; !  boolean NOT\r\n\u001b[82X\u001b[12;3HBoolean flags can be turned on using the values 1, On, True or Yes.\u001b[16X\u001b[13;3HThey can be turned off using the values 0, Off, False or No.\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[15;2H An empty string can be denoted by simply not writing anything after the equal\r\n; sign, or by using the None keyword:\r\n\u001b[55X\u001b[18;3Hfoo =         ; sets foo to an empty string\r\n; foo = None    ; sets foo to an empty string\r\n; foo = \"None\"  ; sets foo to the string 'None'\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[22;3HIf you use constants in your value, and these constants belong to a    \u001b[23;3Hdynamically loaded extension (either a PHP extension or a Zend extension),\u001b[24;2H you may only use these constants *after* the line that loads the extension.\u001b[26;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[59X\u001b[27;3HAbout this file ;\u001b[57X\u001b[28;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[21X\u001b[29;2H PHP comes packaged with two INI files. One that is recommended to be used\r\n; in production environments and one that is recommended to be used in\u001b[31;3Hdevelopment environments.\u001b[57X\r\n\u001b[81X\u001b[33;3Hphp.ini-production contains settings which hold security, performance and\u001b[34;3Hbest practices at its core. But please be aware, these settings may break\u001b[35;3Hcompatibility with older or less security-conscious applications. We\u001b[36;3Hrecommending using the production ini in production and testing environments.\r\n\u001b[31X\n; php.ini-development is very similar to its production variant, except it is\u001b[39;3Hmuch more verbose when it comes to errors. We recommend using the\u001b[19X\u001b[40;3Hdevelopment version only in development environments, as errors shown to\u001b[41;3Happlication users can inadvertently leak otherwise secure information.\r\n\u001b[19X\u001b[43;3HThis is the php.ini-production INI file.\r\n\u001b[21X\u001b[45;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[53X\u001b[46;3HQuick Reference ;\u001b[24X\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f78,1            2\u001b[?112c\u001b[?1002h\u001b[?1006h\r\u001b[12A\u001b[?25h"]
